FBIS3-20121 "drweu059_n_94005" FBIS-WEU-94-059 Document Type:Daily Report 27 Mar 1994 NORDIC COUNTRIES Norway Iranian Diplomat Expelled for Unsuitable Activities LD2703135394 Oslo Radio Norway International in English 1300 GMT 27 Mar 94 LD2703135394 Oslo Radio Norway International Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] An Iranian diplomat has been expelled by the Norwegian Foreign Ministry for so-called activities unsuited to his diplomatic status. Iran's ambassador was informed of the decision on Friday 25 March. Press spokesman Invard Havnen, in the Foreign Ministry, said that the deportation has nothing to do with the assassination attempt on William Nygaard, Norwegian publisher of Salman Rushdie's book, Satanic Verses. The Iranian diplomat has 10 days in which to leave Norway.
